The paper proposes an algorithm for non-negative matrix factorization and provides theoretical guarantees for its recovery under certain conditions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses potential functions, which are commonly used in numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) or scientific computing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with data decomposition, which is a common problem in data science, suggesting that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
